de.javasoft.swing.filter
Interface IRowFilterModel<M>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractRowFilterModel, ComparableRowFilterModel, PatternRowFilterModel, SimpleRowFilterModel
public interface IRowFilterModel<M>

A model capturing state which is converted into a RowFilter. Listeners are notified when changes to the input state effect a change of the RowFilter.

The properties defining its state are

  • columnIndex (immutable): the column identifier
  • match value/s: one or more fixed values to compare against
  • match rule: one ore more logic rules to use in comparisons
Typical clients of this model are view controllers which bind these properties to appropriate input widgets to support dynamic RowFilter creation by users. Currently that's uni-directional view --> rowFilterModel. (Can be expanded into fully by-directional if needed in future). A consequence of directionality is that RowFilterModels cannot be shared across different ColumnFilter instances.

Note for implementors: a RowFilter as defined in core Swing must be strictly immutable. In particular, they must not depend directly on any mutable state stored in the model. Instead, store the state in the RowFilter itself.

Method Detail

getRowFilter

javax.swing.RowFilter<? super M,? super java.lang.Integer> getRowFilter()
Returns the RowFilter as appropriate for the current state. It's a read-and-notify-only bound property, that is the model guarantees to notify registered listeners if the RowFilter property has changed due to any changes in internal state.

Returns:
the RowFilter for the current state, may be null to indicate no filtering

getMatchRules

java.util.List<?> getMatchRules()
Returns a list of match rules know to this model, might be empty but guaranteed to never be null and not having null entries.

Returns:
a List of match rules, never null, might be empty.
See Also:
setMatchRule(Object), getMatchRule()

setMatchRule

void setMatchRule(java.lang.Object matchRule)
Sets the match rule to use in the RowFilter. Allowed are values as returned by getMatchRules(). Implementors are expected to update the RowFilter as appropriate and notify listeners.

Parameters:
matchRule - the rule to use, must not be null.
See Also:
getMatchRule(), getMatchRules()

getMatchRule

java.lang.Object getMatchRule()
Returns the current match rule to use in the RowFilter. Maybe null to indicate that matchRules are not supported. Otherwise it must be an item contained in the List accessible via getMatchRules.

Returns:
the current match rule or null if match rules are not supported.

getMatchRules(), setMatchRule(Object)
